xception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-02T09:15:58.158544+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["LOOCV is a special type of **cross validation** where each data point is used once as a test set.\n","\n","\n","- If you have **N data points**:\n","  - The model is trained **N times**\n","  - Each time:\n","    - **1 data point** is used for testing\n","    - Remaining **N-1 data points** are used for training\n","\n","\n","### Example:\n","For 5 data points:\n","- Train on 4, test on 1 → repeat 5 times\n","\n","\n","### Why it is used:\n","- Uses **maximum data for training**\n","- Gives a **very accurate estimate** of model performance\n","\n","\n","### Advantages:\n","- Low bias (very reliable evaluation)\n","\n","\n","### Disadvantages:\n","- Very **slow and computationally expensive**\n","- Not suitable for large datasets\n","\n","\n","### Summary:\n","- Special case of K-Fold where **K = N**\n","- Best for **small datasets**"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":13,"id":"1393d6b7","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-02T09:15:58.18722Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-02T09:15:58.183853Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-02T09:19:07.923244Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-02T09:19:07.922477Z"},"papermill":{"duration":189.755245,"end_time":"2026-04-02T09:19:07.928889+00:00","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-04-02T09:15:58.173644+00:00","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["LOO R²: -0.0030141464920354633\n"]}],"source":["# from sklearn.model_selection import LeaveOneOut\n","from sklearn.model_selection import LeaveOneOut, cross_val_predict\n","\n","\n","loo=LeaveOneOut()\n","model = LinearRegression()\n","\n","#scores=cross_val_score(model, X, y, cv=loo, scoring='r2')  \n","#We can’t directly use R² on single-sample test sets,\n","\n","y_pred = cross_val_predict(model, X, y, cv=loo)\n","\n","r2 = r2_score(y, y_pred)\n","print(\"LOO R²:\", r2)"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"5822815